ğŸ” Simple Text Encryption & Decryption Tool (Python)

This project is a beginner-friendly Python program that performs simple text encryption and decryption using a randomized substitution cipher.
Every character typed by the user is replaced with a different character based on a shuffled key, making the encrypted message unreadable without the key.

This tool demonstrates:

Character mapping

Basic cryptography concepts

User interaction

Randomized key generation

âœ¨ Features
ğŸ”‘ Random Key Generation

The program builds a list of characters including:

spaces

punctuation

digits

lowercase + uppercase letters

A shuffled version of this list acts as the cipher key

ğŸ” Encryption

Takes user input (plain text)

Replaces each character with its mapped pair from the key

Produces encrypted text that cannot be manually reversed without the key

ğŸ”“ Decryption

Takes encrypted text as input

Uses the key to map each encrypted character back to its original character

Outputs the decrypted (plain) text

ğŸ§­ Interactive Menu

The user can choose:

Encrypt text

Decrypt text

Quit

â–¶ï¸ How to Use

Run the script:

python encryption_tool.py


Sample menu:

***** This is a simple encryption tool *****
What do you wish to do?
1. Encryption of a text
2. Decryption of the text
3. Quit the program
Enter an option(1,2 or 3):


Example encryption:

Your Normal text was    : hello!
Your Encrypted text is  : 4@Zm#


Example decryption:

Your Encrypted text was : 4@Zm#
Your Decrypted text is  : hello!

