ğŸ§  How It Works

A character set is created (letters + digits + punctuation + space)

A shuffled copy acts as the encryption key

Encryption:
plain_text[i] â†’ key[index]

Decryption:
cipher_text[i] â†’ chars[index]

User interacts through a simple looped menu

âš  Note: Since the key is generated at runtime, encrypted text can only be decrypted within the same session.
If the program is restarted, a new key is created, making old encrypted messages unreadable.

ğŸ›  Requirements

Python 3.x

Uses only built-in modules (random, string)

